> > I'd like the script to dynamically output a case
>=20
> Use an array/list and select the nth element from it,
>         nikolai
>=20

I suggest the "select" loop.  For example:

select f in **/*.tex; do
  if [[ "$REPLY" =3D q ]]; then
    break
  elif [[ -n "$f" ]]; then
    gvim $f
  fi
done

Note that this block will loop until you exit with ^C or q.

